  </submap-topicmeta-container><mapref-topicmeta-container class="+ topic/foreign ditaot-d/mapref-topicmeta-container ">
      <navtitle class="- topic/navtitle " xtrc="navtitle:1;34:17" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap">User Guide</navtitle>
    </mapref-topicmeta-container><topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="Understanding markdown-validator" xtrc="topichead:1;20:58" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:1;21:91" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="c_what-is-markdown-validator"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="c_what-is-markdown-validator"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">What is markdown-validator?</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">What is markdown-validator?</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">markdown-validator is a rule-based tool that checks your Markdown files   against editorial standards defined by your team. It catches missing metadata,   incorrect front-matter values, and structural problems before your content reaches   review or publication.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:2;22:85" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/concepts/c_how-validation-works.dita" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="c_how-validation-works"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="c_how-validation-works"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">How validation works</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">How validation works</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">markdown-validator processes your file in three stages: it parses   the front matter and document body, evaluates each rule in the rule set against   your file, and produces a scored report that identifies every rule your file   passes or fails.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:3;23:82" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/concepts/c_validation-levels.dita" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="c_validation-levels"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="c_validation-levels"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Required and Suggested validation levels</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Required and Suggested validation levels</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Every rule in a rule set has a level: <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_validation-levels.dita" xtrc="b:1;23:55">Required</b> or <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_validation-levels.dita" xtrc="b:2;23:74">Suggested</b>.   Required failures block your CI pipeline. Suggested failures appear in the report   as recommendations and do not block a merge.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:4;24:88" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/concepts/c_ci-integration-overview.dita" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="c_ci-integration-overview"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="c_ci-integration-overview"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">How markdown-validator fits into your CI/CD pipeline</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">How markdown-validator fits into your CI/CD pipeline</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">When markdown-validator runs in your CI/CD pipeline, it acts as a   quality gate on every pull request. If any Required rule fails, the pipeline   exits with a non-zero code and blocks the merge until you fix the reported   issues.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:5;25:82" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="c_multiple-rulesets"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="c_multiple-rulesets"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Working with multiple rule sets</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Working with multiple rule sets</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">A single repository can contain content that must meet different   editorial standards — for example, a tutorial section and an API reference   section with distinct metadata requirements. Use separate rule set files and   specify the correct one at runtime with the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;28:55">--rules</codeph>   option.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref></topichead><topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="Get started" xtrc="topichead:2;31:37" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:6;32:78" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/tasks/t_end-to-end-setup.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_end-to-end-setup"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_end-to-end-setup"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Set up markdown-validator from scratch</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Set up markdown-validator from scratch</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">This scenario walks you through the complete setup of   markdown-validator — from installation to a running CI gate — in a single   guided sequence. Follow it top to bottom the first time you set up the tool   for a documentation project.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:7;33:69" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/tasks/t_install.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_install"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_install"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Install markdown-validator</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Install markdown-validator</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Install markdown-validator with pip in a Python virtual environment.   After installation, the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_install.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;24:35">md-validate</codeph> command is available from   your terminal.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:8;34:75" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/tasks/t_download-nltk.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_download-nltk"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_download-nltk"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Download NLTK language data</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Download NLTK language data</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Download the NLTK language corpora required by validation rules   that check sentence counts or part-of-speech tags. You only need to do this   once per Python environment.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref></topichead><topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="Validate documents" xtrc="topichead:3;40:44" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:9;41:82" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/tasks/t_validate-single-file.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_validate-single-file"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_validate-single-file"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Validate a Markdown file from the command line</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Validate a Markdown file from the command line</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Run <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-single-file.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;23:26">md-validate validate</codeph> against a single Markdown   file to check it against your team's rule set. The output shows which rules   passed, which failed, and what you need to change.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:10;42:84" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/tasks/t_read-validation-report.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_read-validation-report"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_read-validation-report"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Read and act on a validation report</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Read and act on a validation report</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">A validation report shows which rules your file passes or fails,   the severity of each failure, and a plain-English mitigation message that tells   you exactly what to fix. This topic walks you through reading the report and   taking action.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:11;43:80" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_validate-directory"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_validate-directory"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Validate a directory of Markdown files</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Validate a directory of Markdown files</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Run <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;23:26">md-validate validate</codeph> with a directory path to   validate all Markdown files in that directory and its subdirectories at once.   Use this before a release or periodic quality review.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:12;44:79" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_set-output-format"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_set-output-format"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Set the output format for validation reports</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Set the output format for validation reports</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Use the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;24:30">--format</codeph> option to choose how   markdown-validator presents its report: plain text for terminal reading,   JSON for CI integration and scripting, or CSV for spreadsheet analysis.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:13;45:74" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/tasks/t_save-reports.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_save-reports"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_save-reports"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Save validation reports to a directory</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Save validation reports to a directory</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Use the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_save-reports.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;23:30">--output</codeph> option to write one report file   per validated document to a directory. This is useful for sharing results with   your team, uploading reports as CI artifacts, or tracking quality over time.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref></topichead><topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="CI/CD integration" xtrc="topichead:4;51:43" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:14;52:86" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/tasks/t_integrate-github-actions.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_integrate-github-actions"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_integrate-github-actions"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Add markdown-validator to a GitHub Actions workflow</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Add markdown-validator to a GitHub Actions workflow</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Create a GitHub Actions workflow file that installs   markdown-validator, downloads NLTK language data, validates your   documentation on every pull request, and uploads reports as downloadable   artifacts.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref></topichead><topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="Reference" xtrc="topichead:5;58:35" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:15;59:67" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="shared/r_quick-reference.dita" type="reference"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="r_quick-reference"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="r_quick-reference"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Quick reference</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Quick reference</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">All operators, flags, workflow step tokens, CLI options, and exit codes   on one page. Use this page when you know what you need and just want the   symbol or syntax.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:16;60:77" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/reference/r_cli-options.dita" type="reference"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="r_cli-options"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="r_cli-options"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">CLI options reference</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">CLI options reference</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Complete reference for all <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/reference/r_cli-options.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;23:49">md-validate</codeph> commands   and options. Use this page to look up the syntax, default values, and effect   of every command-line flag.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:17;61:76" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/reference/r_exit-codes.dita" type="reference"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="r_exit-codes"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="r_exit-codes"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Exit codes reference</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Exit codes reference</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">markdown-validator exits with code <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/reference/r_exit-codes.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;22:57">0</codeph> when all   Required rules pass and code <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/reference/r_exit-codes.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;23:40">1</codeph> when any Required rule fails.   CI systems use these codes to gate pull request merges.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:18;62:79" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide.ditamap" href="user-guide/reference/r_report-output.dita" type="reference"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="r_report-output"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="r_report-output"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Validation report output reference</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Validation report output reference</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Reference for the structure and fields of markdown-validator   validation reports in text, JSON, and CSV format.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref></topichead></submap>

  
  
  
  <submap class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topicgroup ditaot-d/submap " dita-ot:orig-class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/mapref " dita-ot:orig-format="ditamap" dita-ot:orig-href="rule-creator-guide.ditamap" dita-ot:submap-DITAArchVersion="1.3" dita-ot:submap-cascade="merge" dita-ot:submap-class="- map/map " dita-ot:submap-domains="(map mapgroup-d) (topic abbrev-d) (topic delay-d) a(props deliveryTarget) (map ditavalref-d) (map glossref-d) (topic hazard-d) (topic hi-d) (topic indexing-d) (topic markup-d) (topic pr-d) (topic relmgmt-d) (topic sw-d) (topic ui-d) (topic ut-d) (topic markup-d xml-d)" dita-ot:submap-id="rule-creator-guide" dita-ot:submap-specializations="@props/deliveryTarget" dita-ot:submap-xtrc="map:1;8:30" dita-ot:submap-xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" xtrc="mapref:2;41:62" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap"><submap-topicmeta class="+ map/topicmeta ditaot-d/submap-topicmeta "><submap-title class="+ topic/navtitle ditaot-d/submap-title " dita-ot:submap-class="- topic/title " dita-ot:submap-xtrc="title:1;9:10" dita-ot:submap-xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap">Rule Creator Guide</submap-title></submap-topicmeta><submap-topicmeta-container class="+ topic/foreign ditaot-d/submap-topicmeta-container " dita-ot:submap-class="- map/topicmeta " dita-ot:submap-xtrc="topicmeta:1;11:14" dita-ot:submap-xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap">
    <shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc " xtrc="shortdesc:1;12:16" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap">Complete guidance for content leads and editorial teams who
    author, test, and maintain validation rule sets for markdown-validator.</shortdesc>
    <othermeta class="- topic/othermeta " content="rule-creator" name="audience" xtrc="othermeta:1;14:56" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap"/>
  </submap-topicmeta-container><mapref-topicmeta-container class="+ topic/foreign ditaot-d/mapref-topicmeta-container ">
      <navtitle class="- topic/navtitle " xtrc="navtitle:2;43:17" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap">Rule Creator Guide</navtitle>
    </mapref-topicmeta-container><topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="Understanding rule sets" xtrc="topichead:1;20:49" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:1;21:91" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="c_rule-sets-overview"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="c_rule-sets-overview"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Understanding rule sets</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Understanding rule sets</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">A rule set is a JSON file that tells markdown-validator what to   check in a Markdown document. It contains two sections: <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;25:67">rules</codeph>,   which defines individual checks, and <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;26:48">workflows</codeph>, which chains   rules together with conditional logic.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:2;22:85" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-anatomy.dita" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="c_rule-anatomy"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="c_rule-anatomy"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Anatomy of a validation rule</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Anatomy of a validation rule</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Every markdown-validator rule is a JSON object with nine fields.   Understanding what each field does is the foundation for writing rules that   express your editorial standards accurately.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:3;23:99" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_workflow-language-overview.dita" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="c_workflow-language-overview"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="c_workflow-language-overview"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Understanding the workflow step language</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Understanding the workflow step language</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Workflows chain rules together with conditional logic. Use them when   a rule should only run if another rule passes or fails — for example, "check H2   structure only when the document is a tutorial." Simple checks that are always   evaluated do not need workflows.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:4;24:93" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="c_rule-design-patterns"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="c_rule-design-patterns"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Rule design patterns for common editorial checks</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Rule design patterns for common editorial checks</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">These patterns cover the most common editorial requirements you   will need to express as rules. Each pattern includes the JSON, an explanation   of how it works, and common variations.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref></topichead><topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="Author rules" xtrc="topichead:2;30:38" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:5;31:85" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_create-rule-set"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_create-rule-set"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Create a rule set file</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Create a rule set file</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Create a new JSON rule set file that markdown-validator can use to   validate your documentation. Start with a minimal structure and add rules   incrementally.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:6;32:87" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_write-header-rule.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_write-header-rule"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_write-header-rule"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Write a header rule to check front-matter metadata</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Write a header rule to check front-matter metadata</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Header rules check the YAML front-matter metadata at the top of   your Markdown files. Use them to enforce required fields, expected values,   date freshness, and naming patterns.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:7;33:85" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_write-body-rule.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_write-body-rule"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_write-body-rule"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Write a body rule to check document structure</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Write a body rule to check document structure</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Body rules check the content of your Markdown documents — headings,   sections, paragraph structure, and text patterns. They use XPath expressions   to query the rendered HTML. Test your XPath expressions in the REPL before   adding them to a rule.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:8;34:84" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_write-workflow.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_write-workflow"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_write-workflow"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Write a workflow for conditional rule chains</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Write a workflow for conditional rule chains</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">A workflow chains rules together so that some checks only run when   others pass or fail. Write a workflow when your editorial requirement is   conditional — it only applies in specific circumstances.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref></topichead><topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="Test rules" xtrc="topichead:3;40:36" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:9;41:80" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_start-repl.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_start-repl"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_start-repl"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Start the interactive REPL</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Start the interactive REPL</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">The interactive REPL lets you load a Markdown document and explore   its structure, test XPath queries, and evaluate rules interactively. Use it   when writing new rules to confirm your queries return what you expect before   adding them to a rule set.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:10;42:84" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_test-rule-repl.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_test-rule-repl"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_test-rule-repl"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Test a rule in the interactive REPL</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Test a rule in the interactive REPL</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Test a rule in the REPL by running the XPath query against a loaded   document and then evaluating the full rule object. This confirms your rule   will behave as expected before you commit it.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:11;43:88" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_test-workflow-repl.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_test-workflow-repl"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_test-workflow-repl"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Test a workflow in the interactive REPL</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Test a workflow in the interactive REPL</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Testing a workflow requires validating that both the True and False   branches execute correctly. Use the full <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_test-workflow-repl.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;23:52">md-validate validate</codeph>   command with representative documents rather than the REPL   <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_test-workflow-repl.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;25:11">eval</codeph> command, because <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_test-workflow-repl.dita" xtrc="codeph:3;25:50">eval</codeph> tests only a   single rule.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref></topichead><topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="Govern and deploy" xtrc="topichead:4;49:43" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:12;50:88" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-governance.dita" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="c_rule-governance"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="c_rule-governance"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Rule set governance and versioning</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Rule set governance and versioning</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">A rule set is a living document. Good governance practices protect   your authors from unexpected pipeline failures while allowing your editorial   standards to evolve over time.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:13;51:90" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_known-limitations.dita" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="c_known-limitations"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="c_known-limitations"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Known limitations</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Known limitations</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Understanding the current limitations of markdown-validator before   you write rules saves hours of debugging. Four limitations affect the types   of rules you can reliably express today.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:14;52:85" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" type="task"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="t_deploy-rule-set"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="t_deploy-rule-set"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Deploy and version a rule set</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Deploy and version a rule set</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Deploying a rule set means committing it to your documentation   repository, verifying it does not create unexpected failures across existing   content, and communicating any new requirements to your authors.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref></topichead><topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="Reference" xtrc="topichead:5;58:35" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:15;59:85" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/reference/r_rule-fields.dita" type="reference"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="r_rule-fields"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="r_rule-fields"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Rule fields reference</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Rule fields reference</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Complete reference for every field in a rule object. Use this page   to look up allowed values, defaults, and field-level constraints.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:16;60:79" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/reference/r_flags.dita" type="reference"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="r_flags"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="r_flags"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Flags reference</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Flags reference</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">The <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_flags.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;22:26">flag</codeph> field controls how a rule's query result   is processed before comparison. Header and body rules each have their own   flag set.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:17;61:83" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" type="reference"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="r_operators"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="r_operators"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Operators reference</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Operators reference</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">The <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;24:26">operation</codeph> field specifies the comparison   operator applied between the processed query result and the expected   <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;26:11">value</codeph>. The operator returns true (pass) or false   (fail).</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:18;62:88" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/reference/r_workflow-steps.dita" type="reference"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="r_workflow-steps"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="r_workflow-steps"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Workflow step patterns reference</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Workflow step patterns reference</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">A workflow's <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_workflow-steps.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;22:35">steps</codeph> field is a comma-separated string   of <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_workflow-steps.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;23:14">source-target</codeph> tokens. Twelve patterns are recognised.   Combine them to express any conditional rule dependency.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:19;63:87" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide.ditamap" href="rule-creator-guide/reference/r_repl-commands.dita" type="reference"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="r_repl-commands"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="r_repl-commands"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">REPL commands reference</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">REPL commands reference</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Complete reference for all commands available in the   <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_repl-commands.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;23:11">md-validate repl</codeph> interactive session.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref></topichead></submap>

  
  
  
  <topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="Troubleshooting" xtrc="topichead:1;50:41" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:1;51:72" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap" href="troubleshooting/ts_nltk-error.dita" type="troubleshooting"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="ts_nltk-error"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="ts_nltk-error"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Resolve a NLTK LookupError on first run</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Resolve a NLTK LookupError on first run</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">A <systemoutput class="+ topic/ph sw-d/systemoutput " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/troubleshooting/ts_nltk-error.dita" xtrc="systemoutput:1;23:30">LookupError: Resource punkt_tab not found</systemoutput>   error means the NLTK language data required by sentence-count or part-of-speech   rules is not installed on your system.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:2;52:76" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap" href="troubleshooting/ts_no-frontmatter.dita" type="troubleshooting"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="ts_no-frontmatter"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="ts_no-frontmatter"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Resolve a ParseError caused by missing front matter</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Resolve a ParseError caused by missing front matter</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">A <systemoutput class="+ topic/ph sw-d/systemoutput " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/troubleshooting/ts_no-frontmatter.dita" xtrc="systemoutput:1;23:30">ParseError</systemoutput> means markdown-validator   could not find a valid YAML front-matter block at the top of your file.   Every Markdown file must begin with <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/troubleshooting/ts_no-frontmatter.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;25:47">---</codeph> to be   validated.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:3;53:79" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap" href="troubleshooting/ts_rule-never-passes.dita" type="troubleshooting"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="ts_rule-never-passes"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="ts_rule-never-passes"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Debug a rule that never passes on a valid document</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Debug a rule that never passes on a valid document</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">A rule that always fails even on correctly formatted documents   usually has a mismatch between the query result and the expected value.   Use the REPL to inspect the exact values the rule is working with.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:4;54:81" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap" href="troubleshooting/ts_xpath-wrong-results.dita" type="troubleshooting"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="ts_xpath-wrong-results"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="ts_xpath-wrong-results"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Debug an XPath expression that returns unexpected results</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Debug an XPath expression that returns unexpected results</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">XPath queries that seem correct but return unexpected results are   usually caused by the flat HTML structure that markdown-validator produces.   Use the REPL to inspect the actual HTML and adjust your query.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:5;55:70" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap" href="troubleshooting/ts_ci-fails.dita" type="troubleshooting"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="ts_ci-fails"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="ts_ci-fails"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Resolve a validation failure in a CI/CD pipeline</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Resolve a validation failure in a CI/CD pipeline</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">When the validation step in your CI pipeline fails, your pull request   is blocked. This topic shows you how to find the failure report, reproduce the   failure locally, and resolve the specific issue.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref></topichead>

  
  
  
  <topichead class="+ map/topicref mapgroup-d/topichead " navtitle="Reference" xtrc="topichead:2;61:35" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap"><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:6;62:67" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap" href="shared/r_quick-reference.dita" type="reference"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="r_quick-reference"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="r_quick-reference"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Quick reference</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Quick reference</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">All operators, flags, workflow step tokens, CLI options, and exit codes   on one page. Use this page when you know what you need and just want the   symbol or syntax.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref class="- map/topicref " format="dita" xtrc="topicref:7;63:58" xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/markdown-validator.ditamap" href="shared/glossary.dita" type="glossgroup"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="glossary"><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="glossary"/><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Glossary</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Glossary</linktext></topicmeta></topicref></topichead>

</map>